  "text": "For the [4SU]Na + complex, the ground-state structure, 4, generated by ESI was found [CITATION_1] to be the 2-keto-4-sulfhydryl tautomer of 4SU, where the sulfhydryl hydrogen atom is directed away from the N3 group and Na + is bound to the O2 and N3 atoms, as shown in Scheme 5. The first-excited conformer, 4a, is 3.9 kJ/mol higher in free energy and the hydrogen atom is oriented toward the N3 atom. The results obtained [CITATION_2] indicate that these structures are spectroscopically indistinguishable because their calculated IR spectra are virtually the same.",
